Deputy Justice Minister John Jeffery says fathers who fail to pay maintenance for their children will be blacklisted from obtaining any loans. JOHANNESBURG - Deputy Justice Minister John Jeffery says fathers who fail to pay maintenance for their children will be blacklisted from obtaining any loans.He s addressed a large crowd of Soshanguve residents, the majority of them women, at an event aimed at raising awareness around child and women abuse.Jeffrey has warned that fathers who neglect their children will have to face financial consequences. We ve introduced stricter measures to enforce maintenance recovery, including the blacklisting of people who continue to default. He says both parents have a mutual responsibility to raise their children in a just and acceptable manner.Over 60 maintenance applicants here have received money obtained from fathers.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)